post_text:
Just in time for back-to-school, newly tenured staff received gifts of books or baskets filled with office supplies from the Curriculum and Instruction Department. Angela College, a professional learning coordinator, came up with the idea to do something special to commemorate the important milestone.

“I wanted to recognize their work,” said Angela, who also gave them handwritten notes of encouragement with their gifts. “This is a way to say we appreciate your efforts, your time and it’s something you can use in your role,” Angela said.

Armstrong teacher, Grant Brakob, said the baskets were both appreciated and perfect.

Staff in photos:
Tim Leach, special ed teacher Robbinsdale Middle School
Jorge Guiral, 4th grade, RSIS Robbinsdale Spanish Immersion
Lyndsey Tisch - social worker, Neill Elementary
#Rdale281

Thanks to everyone who volunteered their time to help our Zachary Lane veggie gardens/outdoor learning space become a reality! Have a bored Middle Schooler at home? Middle School Summer Enrichment is happening now!
Sign on whatever days you would like through July 31st!

To access:
1. Login to Schoology
2. Select Courses in the top menu.
3. Click Join a Course or My Courses.
4. From the My Courses page, click Join Course on the right side of the page.
5. Enter your access code 9K8Q-7JZ2-PRN5H .
6. Click Join

Please call 504.763.8573 or email ned_nelson@rdale.org if you have any questions.

Have you heard about our Elementary Summer Enrichment Program? The program includes three weeks of learning activities for K-5 grade students from July 13 - 31! 9 AM- 1 PM Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays! Projects are completed independently at home at your own pace with teachers available for support. Participation is flexible, you can access the materials for full three weeks or just a few of the days. Materials and teacher info can be accessed beginning July 9th at https://Bit.ly/281Summer2020

Printed materials are also available on July 9 or 14th from 9 am - 1 pm at Lakeview, Northport, SEA, or Forest.

Contact Kim Henke at 763-504-7856 for more information.
Forest Elementary Lakeview Elementary School Meadow Lake Elementary School Neill Elementary Noble Elementary Northport Elementary School Sonnesyn Elementary Zachary Lane Elementary FAIR School Pilgrim Lane SEA School of Engineering and Arts Robbinsdale Spanish Immersion School

Robbinsdale Area Schools Early Childhood Programs
July 15 at 3:07 PM ·

Thank you to everyone who visited us at Cooper and Northport today! We were able to distribute 200 summer learning kits, 250 children’s masks and hundreds of children’s books!

Thank you to the staff, volunteers, Rockford Road Library, The Free Book Buggie and Cornerstone Church Crystal for partnering with us to make this event happen.

As some of you know, we ran out of learning kits at Cooper. We apologize for any inconvenience. For anyone who is interested, here are links to the activity cards that were included in the learning kits:

English: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1d85PSagdShSJpE29QU6wzDXwFS4fuyyd/view?usp=sharing

Spanish: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1rnl_DnaPUeARyXrP1S36ioK3UTgYisHl/view?usp=sharing

Sign on whatever days you would like through July 31st!

To access:
1. Login to Schoology
2. Select Courses in the top menu.
3. Click Join a Course or My Courses.
4. From the My Courses page, click Join Course on the right side of the page.
5. Enter your access code 9K8Q-7JZ2-PRN5H .
6. Click Join

Please call 504.763.8573 or email ned_nelson@rdale.org if you have any questions.

post_text: Thank you to our Nutritional Services staff for the fun holiday treat! #Rdale281
shared_text:
Robbinsdale Nutrition Services
July 1 at 8:07 AM ·

We've got something fun for 4th of July weekend! Today at Robbinsdale Cooper High School and Northport Elementary, we'll be handing out Strawberry Rhubarb Sauce kits! Each bag contains strawberries, a lemon, and delicious locally grown rhubarb from Lenny Xiong's farm in Cannon Falls via The Good Acre. And thanks to the fabulous Molly Harris Libra, one of our very own at Robbinsdale Area Schools, we have a delightful video tutorial! We serve from 10:30am-noon or until we are out today! #farmtoschool #trayblazers #cookingwithkids #FFVP #TogetherWeAre281

post_text: Thank you to our RSI community for giving back to those in need! #rdale281
shared_text:
Robbinsdale Spanish Immersion School
June 9 at 2:59 PM ·

What an incredible community we have! Over 150 bags of food and toiletries were donated during our final curbside pickup. We chose to partner with Bancroft because of the connection we have through Sra. DePaz. Her husband, Diego DePaz, is the principal at Bancroft, located just four blocks from George Floyd’s fatal encounter. Last Thursday, Sr. and Sra. DePaz, Sr. Brown, Sra. Evans and I brought the bags to Bancroft for their final curbside pickup. We understand that the needs will continue into the fall, and we look forward to partnering with Bancroft Elementary again soon. Thank you so, so much for your continued generosity!

Robbinsdale Nutrition Services
June 5 at 11:59 AM ·

P-EBT is for students who are normally able to get free or reduced-price school meals. Apply and get up to $325 per child to spend on groceries. Please note, children may continue to receive "grab n go" meals or emergency food at COVID-19 emergency feeding sites offered by schools and community locations, even if they are receiving P-EBT benefits. Applications are separate from the school meal benefits application and you can apply online at the link starting June 8th at noon. Robbinsdale Nutrition Services does not have anything to do with this program but wanted to pass it along, so direct questions to P-EBT hotline at 651-431-4050 or 800-657-3698. https://mn.p-ebt.org/en/

post_text: We care. Stay home. Stay safe. #Rdale281 #StaySafeMN
shared_text:
City of New Hope
June 1 at 2:35 PM ·

The city of New Hope has extended city-wide curfews for two additional days.

The city-wide curfew is in effect tonight, Monday, June 1 at 10 p.m. until tomorrow, Tuesday, June 2 at 4 a.m. and again Tuesday, June 2 at 10 p.m. until Wednesday, June 3 at 4 a.m.

During the hours of the curfew, all persons must not travel on any public street or in any public place. All law enforcement, fire, medical personnel, as well other personnel as authorized by the City, County, State, or Federal jurisdictions are exempt from the curfew. Individuals seeking emergency care, fleeing dangerous circumstances, experiencing homelessness, and having to travel to and from employment are also exempt.

shared_text:
City of Golden Valley, MN - Local Government
June 1 at 5:00 PM ·

The Golden Valley Police Department (GVPD) continues to have additional officers on duty and has more than enough resources ready to handle regular 911 calls and any other incidents should they arise. The Department continues to work with other agencies and monitor the situation. The GVPD will update the community again later tonight.

The GVPD also wants to remind residents of the extended city-wide nighttime curfew consistent with Governor Walz’s announcement of the curfew extension for Minneapolis and St Paul. It is in effect from tonight at 10 pm until Tuesday at 4 am, and again from 10 pm Tuesday, June 2 until 4 am Wednesday, June 3. Thank you to all residents for observing the curfew over the weekend.

As always, the GVPD relies on residents to help be its eyes and ears. Please call 911 for any emergency services and to report suspicious activity. You may remain anonymous.
https://www.goldenvalleymn.gov/newsarchive/index.php/2020/06/01/gvpd-issues-situational-awareness-brief-9/

Seven Dreams Education Foundation
May 27 at 3:48 PM ·

Donate to the TOGETHER, WE ARE 281 fundraiser for Robbinsdale Area Schools! Because of unprecedented demands that COVID-19 has placed on our school district, Seven Dreams is hosting a one-time fundraiser to directly benefit our schools. With urgent needs related to distance learning, and decreased revenue, our students and staff need your help! Funds raised through this effort will be used where the greatest needs exist, including, but not limited to:
• technology and Internet access
• social and emotional mental health
• tools for academic support
DONATE at: http://bidpal.net/togetherweare281 or find this link on our website at: https://www.sevendreams.org/donate

post_text: We are so proud of our students for helping those in our community during this time! #rdale281 #Togetherweare281
shared_text:
Adult Academic Program - Robbinsdale Area Schools
May 8 at 3:32 PM ·

Over the school year, Barbara’s Level 4 ELL students had been going on regular visits to Covenant Village Retirement Home of Golden Valley. During each visit, the students and a group of seniors would have discussions, play games, and complete crafts & projects. Earlier in the school year, the seniors even had a chance to visit Barbara’s students in their classroom. To wrap up their year-long partnership, one of Barbara’s students, Suzi, collected donations from General Mills, made goody bags, and greeting cards for each of the seniors who participated. The kind gesture was the students’ way to send their thoughts and love to the seniors during this difficult time. Nice work, everyone!

We are so proud of our students for helping those in our community during this time! #rdale281 #Togetherweare281

Congratulations to Seniors Jack Major and Harry Latimore for winning $100 each for being named finalists in the 2020 Minneapolis Federal Reserve Bank Essay Contest! Jack and Harry are still in the running for the top prize which is an additional $400 and a Summer internship at the Fed that will be announced at a virtual awards ceremony next week. post_text: So inspiring to see students like Michelle helping to make a difference in our community! #Rdaleproud #Rdale281
shared_text:
Woodchuck USA
April 14 at 12:49 PM ·

Some positive PPE news for your Tuesday!



We have hundreds of incredible people working around the clock here at WOODCHUCK USA. They're working hard to get millions of face shields into the hands of our doctors, nurses, and medical professionals on the front lines. Today we wanted to take a minute to highlight one of the front line heroes on our team, who is pushing in true "Beast mode" fashion to help save lives.



Our team has already shipped millions of face shields across the United States to our amazing front line care providers. These production numbers continue to climb each week as it remains our teams sole priority to get these life saving supplies into the hands of our front line providers.



If you are aware of anyone in need of live saving PPE, please contact our team: sales@woodchuckusa.com , or call us directly at 833.828.4980

post_text: Robbinsdale Middle School teachers are giving back to our community in a big way. Thank you! #Rdale281
shared_text:
Robbinsdale Middle School
April 8 at 7:12 AM ·

Robbinsdale Middle School Gateway to Technology teachers are 3D printing splitters that can be used for ventilators in hospitals. One of the biggest concerns is that there may not be enough ventilators for people that will need assistance breathing due to the COVID-19 virus. The splitters will allow one ventilator to be used for 2 or 4 patients. These splitters will be donated to Project CURE (projectcure.org) and distributed to hospitals in need.

post_text:
We thank you for your continued patience and support as we navigate these unprecedented times. While Technology Services has planned for increased capacity and utilization of our online learning platforms, we are continuing to see periodic disruptions in Schoology and Seesaw services. Please note these service disruptions are occurring across the country.

According to our Schoology account rep, Schoology has seen a usage increase of 400 percent since distance learning began, which has added strain on certain areas within Schoology. This had caused interruptions to specific spaces within the site. Schoology has identified the factors that led to this negative impact on some users’ experience and have taken measures to correct them.

post_text:
Dear Robbinsdale Area Schools Families and Staff,

As our school community navigates unprecedented times, our staff has worked diligently to prepare for supporting continuity of education through a distance learning model. While Technology Services has planned for increased capacity and utilization of our online learning platforms, there may be some bumps in the road. This morning, there were periodic disruptions in Schoology and Seesaw services across the country. The current reliance on technology around the world continues to tax telecommunications infrastructure. As schools across Minnesota (and our country) utilize Distance Learning, and more employees work remotely, we may experience widespread slowdowns and intermittent outages. Our technology staff continue to work diligently to ensure our systems support our students and families during this time.

To address the potential for technology slowdowns, teachers and staff have been asked to provide both technology-based and offline activities. We appreciate your continued patience, support and partnership.

Seven Dreams Education Foundation
December 18, 2019 at 7:21 PM ·

At this year's Bird Bash gala event on February 8, 2020, we will raise money to fund a well-researched program called SECOND STEP that teaches students "social emotional" skills through interactive games, activities and media. It is used in schools throughout the Twin Cities, U.S. and world - and in a few RAS classrooms. Here's Sarah Jaremko at NEILL ELEMENTARY teaching a Second Step lesson today called "Introduction to Emotion Management!" Help us raise at least $50,000 at the Bird Bash to roll it out in ALL of our elementary and middle schools. Professional development is included. Learn more at https://www.secondstep.org/second-step-social-emotional-learning. Buy your tickets for the Bird Bash today at: www.bidpal.net/birdbash2020

Tickets for our 7th annual BIRD BASH gala event are now on sale! The event is SATURDAY, FEBRUARY 8, 2020 at the Marriott Northwest in Brooklyn Park. Join us for dinner, entertainment, silent & live auctions as we raise funds for Robbinsdale Area Schools! This year, we will be funding an important mental health program that will equip all elementary and middle school students with powerful tools to manage their emotions, make responsible decisions, and be compassionate, respectful people. Tickets are on sale now for $75 at www.bidpal.net/birdbash2020
or contact Emily@sevendreams.org for more information. The event sells out, so purchase your tickets today!

Robbinsdale Cooper High School added 28 new photos to the album: Veterans Breakfast at Cooper High School — at Robbinsdale Cooper High School.
November 2019 · New Hope, MN ·

Today the Cooper Student Council hosted the first "Cooper Honors Our Veterans" breakfast. The Veteran guests were entertained by the Cooper band and choir. Cooper cheerleaders greeted our guests. Cooper students wrote Thank You cards and our local YMCA preschoolers made artifacts for them. Veterans from WWII to present day were able to join us. Thank you for your service.

Robbinsdale Armstrong High School
September 16, 2019 at 6:53 AM ·

Five AHS Junior Student Council Representatives will attend the 2019 High School Blood Drive Workshop hosted by the Memorial Blood Center.
This is a one-day training and education session that provides Student Blood Drive Coordinators a hands-on opportunity to expand their knowledge about blood-what it is, what it does, and why donors are so critical to saving and sustaining lives. They will hear first-hand from a blood recipient and the hone leadership and customer service skills to run a successful blood drive.

The Armstrong Student Council is honored to host the the 2019-2020 Armstrong Blood Drives on Friday, November 8th and Friday, February 21st Students will receive communication that will provide information and allow them to register to donate. Let's GIVE Falcons!!!

Pictured: Margot Maxwell, Miriam Manna, Tori Thomas, Evan Dimich, Matthew Shapiro

post_text:
Today was our District Opener for teachers and staff! We were honored to have special guest speaker, Minnesota's First Lady Gwen Walz, give the keynote address.

The event started with a flag presentation by the Boy Scouts, and Robbinsdale Armstrong High School senior Sara Shiff wowed with an amazing vocal performance of the National Anthem.

The Robbinsdale Cooper High School Drumline and high school cheer squads did a fabulous job leading our new teachers and staff into the packed auditorium.

Thank you to Chair Vento, RFT President Eckhoff, Director Boone and Superintendent Jenkins for their remarks.

It's going to be a great year! #Rdale281

Attention families: Fall letters from Robbinsdale Nutrition Services went out recently. Unfortunately, there was an error on the letters and student ID numbers were inadvertently used as lunch keypad/pin numbers.
